%N A037660 Base 4 digits are, in order, the first n terms of the periodic sequence with initial period 3,1,0.
%H A037660 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (4,0,1,-4).
%F A037660 G.f.: x*(3+x) / ( (x-1)*(4*x-1)*(1+x+x^2) ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Apr 30 2015
%F A037660 a(n) = 4*a(n-1) + a(n-3) - 4*a(n-4). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 02 2023
%F A037660 a(n) = floor(52*4^n/63). - _Christian Krause_, Jun 06 2026
%F A037660 E.g.f.: 2*exp(-x/2)*(-14*exp(3*x/2) + 26*exp(9*x/2) - 12*cos(sqrt(3)*x/2) - sqrt(3)*sin(sqrt(3)*x/2))/63. - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 06 2026
